Second Corinthians 2:10-11.
If the Apostle says he has forgiven what the laypeople have forgiven, how will what a bishop has done be rejected?

213
00:24:55,440 --> 00:25:03,844
So, neither baptism, forgiveness of sins, nor the renewal of the body has been granted to his holy authority because nothing has been commanded by his own usurpation.

214
00:25:03,844 --> 00:25:06,173
All of it has flowed from apostolic authority.

215
00:25:06,173 --> 00:25:15,540
