So neither the one who plants nor the one who waters is anything, but only God who gives the growth.

793
01:19:38,487 --> 01:19:39,534
1 Corinthians 3:6-7.

794
01:19:39,534 --> 01:19:45,974
Therefore, whether we baptize, compel to repentance, or grant forgiveness to the repentant, we do it by Christ's authority.

795
01:19:45,974 --> 01:19:50,059
You must consider whether Christ can do this and whether Christ has done this.

796
01:19:50,059 --> 01:19:55,086
If forgiveness of sins could be given to the repentant, you say, then baptism was not necessary.

797
01:19:55,086 --> 01:19:56,866
This is a very foolish comparison!

798
01:19:56,866 --> 01:20:03,202
For baptism is the sacrament of the Lord’s passion; the forgiveness for the repentant is the merit of the one confessing.

799
01:20:03,202 --> 01:20:07,862
Everyone can obtain the former because it is a gift of God’s grace; that is, a free gift.

800
01:20:07,862 --> 01:20:16,397
But this labor is for the few who rise again after a fall, who recover after wounds, who are aided by tearful cries, who revive after the destruction of the flesh.

801
01:20:16,397 --> 01:20:22,262
You claim that I have wrongly cited the example where God says: I prefer a sinner's repentance over their death.

802
01:20:22,262 --> 01:20:22,995
Ezekiel 33:11.

803
01:20:22,995 --> 01:20:29,854
What if I had added the passage from Isaiah: When you turn and groan, then you will be saved and you will know where you have been?

804
01:20:29,854 --> 01:20:32,054
Isaiah 30:15, according to the Septuagint.

805
01:20:32,054 --> 01:20:38,389
What if I had quoted from Revelation: Remember where you have fallen from, and repent, and do the works you did at first?

806
01:20:38,389 --> 01:20:39,175
Revelation 2:5.

807
01:20:39,175 --> 01:20:42,474
You might say these were spoken to the Gentiles before baptism.

808
01:20:42,474 --> 01:20:47,710
Listen to the Apostle: We know that whatever the law says, it speaks to those who are under the law.

809
01:20:47,710 --> 01:20:48,338
Romans 3:19.

810
01:20:48,338 --> 01:20:52,946
Therefore, those who lived without the law are not bound by the condition of repentance.

811
01:20:52,946 --> 01:20:58,444
Even if they had repented, they did so freely by faith, not by the bond of repentance imposed by the law.

812
01:20:58,444 --> 01:21:02,895
So then, you might say, Jews who repented before baptism cannot repent after baptism.

813
01:21:02,895 --> 01:21:04,990
Who taught you this, brother Sympronian?

814
01:21:04,990 --> 01:21:08,917
Who suggested that one who has repented before should not repent afterward?

815
01:21:08,917 --> 01:21:10,540
But we will discuss this later.

816
01:21:10,540 --> 01:21:20,856
Meanwhile, if repentance was denied to Jews after baptism because they fulfilled it before, at least grant that the Gentiles, who did not know the law of repentance before, should repent afterward.

817
01:21:20,856 --> 01:21:24,102
But even regarding the Jews, I do not want you to be mistaken.

818
01:21:25,463 --> 01:21:32,310
They repented earlier because they had corrupted the old baptism and were repenting as if they had betrayed their faith after believing.

819
01:21:32,310 --> 01:21:52,145
Listen to the Apostle: "For I do not want you to be ignorant, brothers, that our ancestors were all under the cloud and all passed through the sea, and all were baptized into Moses in the cloud and in the sea. They all ate the same spiritual food and drank the same spiritual drink; for they drank from the spiritual rock that followed them, and the rock was Christ" (First Corinthians 10:1-4).

820
01:21:52,145 --> 01:21:55,165
They had violated this baptism, and therefore they repented.

821
01:21:55,165 --> 01:21:59,998
If the remission of sins could be given to those who repent, you say, baptism was not necessary.

822
01:21:59,998 --> 01:22:01,307
What a foolish comparison!

