968
01:40:49,361 --> 01:40:53,279
And again: "These are a shadow of the good things to come" (Hebrews 10:1).

969
01:40:53,279 --> 01:41:00,639
Certainly, you agree that these things were said to tax collectors and sinners, that is, the humble people, and therefore the younger ones.

970
01:41:00,639 --> 01:41:03,763
So tell me: is the Christian people itself the younger one?

971
01:41:03,763 --> 01:41:05,722
Have they been grafted into the root?

972
01:41:05,722 --> 01:41:07,364
Have they joined those members?

973
01:41:07,364 --> 01:41:14,512
Built, as it is written, on the foundation of the apostles and prophets, with Christ Jesus Himself as the cornerstone (Ephesians 2:20).

974
01:41:14,512 --> 01:41:16,153
Is He the God of the Jews only?

975
01:41:16,153 --> 01:41:18,218
Is He not also the God of the Gentiles?

976
01:41:18,218 --> 01:41:19,595
Yes, also of the Gentiles.

977
01:41:19,595 --> 01:41:24,520
Since there is one God who justifies the ungodly by faith and through faith (Romans 3:29-30).

978
01:41:25,631 --> 01:41:30,967
Surely that humble people, whom God compared to a coin, the younger son, and a little sheep, was the Church.

979
01:41:30,967 --> 01:41:35,166
From this came the whole crowd of believers, from which the Christian people emerged.

980
01:41:35,166 --> 01:43:19,005
Our members are also joined to this body, all portions of believers, so that they might be grafted into the good olive tree from the wild olive tree of the nations, as the Apostle says: "Partakers of its richness" in the book of Romans chapter eleven, verse seventeen. And so, we all might be one in Christ, Jew and Greek, slave and free, as stated in Galatians chapter three, verse twenty-eight. Therefore, if we are one body with those humble ones, the words spoken to the humble of old are also spoken to us. Thus, whatever was preached about a part of the body was announced to the whole body.
Let me be clearer. That later people, that poor, that average, was an image of the Church, a humble and modest soul, a soul freed by Christ. The Lord came to save this, did not leave it in hell: this is the sheep carried back on the shoulders, that is, by the effort and strength of patience. This is the coin that is sought and shown to the neighbors when found. Do you see how its form matches the likeness of the repentant? Do you see mercy extending to this time? Do you see that whatever was said to the nascent Church pertains to the fullness of the Church? Hence, the Lord added there: "There will be joy in heaven over one sinner who repents, more than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need repentance" as found in Luke chapter fifteen, verse seven. For if all those things were written to remind us, to whom then will that humble sinner people be compared, if not to the repentant people? And if the figures recur in order, the ninety-nine healthy represent the whole Church. The one wandering is the portion of the delinquent, and the lost coin is that miserable sinner. Returning after his wrongs, he is considered similar to the redeemed one. Now you see rightly placed by me, when I was dealing with the cure of the repentant, that the Lord said: "Those who are well have no need of a physician, but those who are sick" in Matthew chapter nine, verse twelve. Rightly also: "Blessed are those who mourn, for they shall be comforted" as stated in Matthew chapter five, verse five.

981
01:43:19,103 --> 01:43:24,401
Whatever has been said about tax collectors and sinners will apply to all the sick and all the wretched.

982
01:43:24,401 --> 01:43:31,888
Let me speak more clearly: that latter group of people, the poor, the average, represents the Church, a humble and modest soul liberated by Christ.

983
01:43:31,888 --> 01:43:40,395
The Lord came to save this soul and did not leave it in hell: this is the sheep that is brought back on the shoulders, that is, by the effort and strength of patience.

984
01:43:40,395 --> 01:43:44,215
This is the coin that is sought and, once found, is shown to the neighbors.

985
01:43:44,215 --> 01:43:47,016
Do you see how its form matches the image of penitents?

986
01:43:47,016 --> 01:43:49,308
Do you see how mercy extends up to this time?

987
01:43:49,308 --> 01:43:54,096
Do you see that whatever was said to the nascent Church applies to the fullness of the Church?

988
01:43:54,096 --> 01:44:02,602
Hence, the Lord added: So there will be joy in heaven over one sinner who repents, more than over ninety-nine righteous persons who do not need repentance (Luke 15:7).

989
01:44:02,602 --> 01:44:09,173
If all those things were written to remind us, to whom will that humble sinful people be compared, if not to the penitent people?

990
01:44:09,173 --> 01:44:22,977
And if in recurring figures, the ninety-nine healthy ones represent the whole Church; the one wandering represents the portion of the delinquent; and the lost coin is the miserable sinner: the returning son after his wrongdoings is considered similar to the redeemed one.

991
01:44:22,977 --> 01:44:31,585
