1148
02:08:34,399 --> 02:08:38,046
The gates of paradise are open; with the sword yielding, penetrate.

1149
02:08:38,046 --> 02:08:41,965
With so many of our people confessing the one God, close off your gifts.

1150
02:08:41,965 --> 02:08:48,552
But if circumstances are far different and your cruelty prevails, now you understand, Novatians, that God can have mercy.

1151
02:08:48,552 --> 02:08:53,940
Now, let the medicine, though late, be available to our unfortunate brothers confessing their past.

1152
02:08:53,940 --> 02:08:58,785
Now, the one wounded and neglected by the Levite and priest can be healed through Christ.

1153
02:08:58,785 --> 02:09:02,269
Now, the prayers of the Church must not be denied to the humble.

1154
02:09:02,269 --> 02:09:06,351
Now, the hands of the priests must be extended to these miserable brothers.

1155
02:09:06,351 --> 02:09:14,516
We understand your reproach, but the Church of God is a dove, not bitter with gall, not violent with tearing claws, even with small and tiny feathers.

1156
02:09:14,516 --> 02:09:25,185
We also know the well of living water and the sealed fountain, untainted by the filth of a heretic's whirlpool, and the enclosed garden full of great and small vegetables, both cheap and precious.

1157
02:09:25,185 --> 02:09:33,023
Consider the eight souls from the ark, among them Ham, and those thousands of birds and beasts, clean and unclean alike, by pairs and by sevens.

1158
02:09:33,023 --> 02:09:39,936
We think of the dry fountains and the clouds stirred by whirlwinds as the sterility of heretics and the force of insane voices.

1159
02:09:39,936 --> 02:09:54,687
We do not promise freedom while we ourselves are slaves to punishment; but having confessed our crimes, we urge others to confess as well and to believe in Him who justifies the ungodly by faith Romans 3:26, who reverses the judgment imposed against wickedness Joel 2:13.

1160
02:09:54,687 --> 02:09:59,586
We also heed the false prophets and ravenous wolves, as we guard against you Matthew 7:15.

1161
02:09:59,586 --> 02:10:04,104
We remember Jannes and Jambres who opposed Moses, just as you oppose the Catholics.

1162
02:10:04,104 --> 02:10:09,547
Thus the Apostle says: Just as Jannes and Jambres opposed Moses, so these men also oppose the truth.

1163
02:10:09,547 --> 02:10:18,257
They are men of corrupt minds, disapproved by God; but they will not get very far, for their folly will be plain to all, as was that of those two men 2 Timothy.

1164
02:10:19,127 --> 02:10:24,599
It is clear that you have been criticized for your inability to improve and for displaying your foolishness.

1165
02:10:24,599 --> 02:10:32,706
What good does it do to maintain a proud and harsh demeanor, to carry yourself with arrogance, to turn away from those in need, and to close your ears and eyes?

1166
02:10:32,706 --> 02:10:34,175
Have you never made mistakes?

1167
02:10:34,175 --> 02:10:35,898
Is there no flaw in your thinking?

1168
02:10:35,898 --> 02:10:37,469
No imperfection in your vision?

1169
02:10:37,469 --> 02:10:40,610
Who can truly claim to have a pure heart or be free from sins?

1170
02:10:40,610 --> 02:10:42,738
Proverbs 20:9 according to the Septuagint.

1171
02:10:42,738 --> 02:10:50,287
I believe you are just, benevolent, temperate, with all your limbs healthy and your whole body intact, not needing a doctor or medicine for ailments.

1172
02:10:50,287 --> 02:10:56,874
Enter heaven now; pass through the gates of paradise with confidence; and keep your gifts from those who confess the one true God.

1173
02:10:56,874 --> 02:11:02,802
If reality is far harsher and your unforgiving cruelty persists, then understand, Novatians, that God can show mercy.

1174
02:11:02,802 --> 02:11:07,109
For the brothers who confess their past sins, even late, let the remedy be available.

1175
02:11:07,109 --> 02:11:11,517
Now, the one wounded and ignored by the Levite and priest can be healed through Christ.

1176
02:11:11,517 --> 02:11:18,610
Now, the prayers of the Church should not be denied to the humble, and the hands of the priests should be extended to the pitiable brothers.

1177
02:11:18,610 --> 02:11:25,298
We, however, understand, as you criticize, that the Church of God is like a dove, not bitter or violent, even if small and delicate.

1178
02:11:25,298 --> 02:11:34,266
We also know the well of living water and the sealed fountain, untainted by the heretic's stain, and the enclosed garden full of various plants, both insignificant and valuable.

1179
02:11:34,266 --> 02:11:40,194
Eight souls were saved in the ark, including Ham, along with thousands of birds and animals, clean and unclean alike.

1180
02:11:40,194 --> 02:11:46,173
But we see the dry springs and stormy clouds as symbols of the sterility of heretics and the rage of senseless voices.

1181
02:11:46,173 --> 02:11:49,567
We do not promise freedom, as we ourselves are bound by punishment.

1182
02:11:49,567 --> 02:11:55,445
But having confessed our sins, we encourage others to confess and believe in Him who justifies the ungodly by faith.

1183
02:11:55,445 --> 02:11:55,749
Romans

1184
02:11:56,711 --> 02:12:01,588
Who reverses a decision against the malice inflicted (Joel 2:13, according to the Septuagint).

1185
02:12:01,588 --> 02:12:06,204
We guard against false prophets and ravenous wolves when we beware of you (Matthew 7:15).

1186
02:12:06,204 --> 02:12:10,769
Indeed, we believe that Jannes and Jambres resisted Moses, just as you resist Catholics.

1187
02:12:10,769 --> 02:12:17,928
The Apostle states: Just as Jannes and Jambres resisted Moses, so do these resist the truth—people with corrupt minds and rejected by God.

1188
02:12:17,928 --> 02:12:24,983
But they will not get very far, for their foolishness will be obvious to everyone, just as that of those men was (Second Timothy 3:8-9).

1189
02:12:24,983 --> 02:12:29,444
This clearly applies to you, who cannot advance any further nor hide your foolishness.

1190
02:12:29,444 --> 02:12:33,231
He who is baptized by a dead person gains nothing (Ecclesiasticus 34:30).

1191
02:12:33,231 --> 02:12:39,196
Similarly, he who is washed in a heretical font, or anointed with a sinner's oil, is filled with an unclean spirit.

1192
02:12:39,196 --> 02:12:41,375
Therefore, you will also be sons of blood.

1193
02:12:41,375 --> 02:12:44,280
For you desire not the peace of the brothers, but blood.

1194
02:12:44,280 --> 02:12:45,784
Your belief is a false faith.

1195
02:12:45,784 --> 02:12:55,173
An adulterous woman is like a heretical congregation:
For the Catholic Church, from the beginning, has not left her husband's bed and chamber, nor desired other lovers or strangers.

1196
02:12:55,173 --> 02:13:07,727
You have painted an exiled image with a new color;
you have separated your bed from the ancient union;
you have distanced yourself from the body of the one-bedded mother, adorned with new methods of pleasing and new enticements of corruption.

1197
02:13:07,727 --> 02:13:27,543
When you propose the most blessed Cyprian as a witness against me, because in the Epistle concerning the Lapsed, he says that Moses, Daniel, and Job prayed for sinners and did not obtain what they asked for, with the Lord saying:
And if three men were in the midst of them, Noah, Job, and Daniel, they would not save sons or daughters, but they alone would be saved (Ezekiel 14:20).

1198
02:13:27,543 --> 02:13:32,886
If only you would rely on Cyprian as a witness, if only you would agree with such healthful sentiments.

1199
02:13:32,886 --> 02:13:45,231
For he, when he urged the lapsed to repentance who did not want to repent, saying that they had received peace from confessors or martyrs, taught and showed that even those patriarchs would not obtain anything for those who do not repent.

1200
02:13:45,231 --> 02:13:47,358
Indeed, who can free an unwilling person?

1201
02:13:47,358 --> 02:13:49,278
Who can humble himself for the proud?

1202
02:13:50,159 --> 02:13:52,428
Who can intercede for those who do not repent?

1203
02:13:52,428 --> 02:13:56,029
When he said this, he was urging them towards the remedies of repentance.

1204
02:13:56,029 --> 02:14:03,229
A man of such seriousness and merit did not speak against himself but taught that sinners should offer prayers and practice confession diligently.

1205
02:14:03,229 --> 02:14:09,197
Cyprian’s own examples illustrate this, recalling that neither Moses nor other saints were able to intercede for sinners.

1206
02:14:09,197 --> 02:14:11,565
Those who are baptized by the dead gain nothing.

1207
02:14:11,565 --> 02:14:22,316
As it is written in Ecclesiasticus thirty-four, verse thirty: “Indeed, those who are washed in the font of heretics are like those anointed with the oil of sinners, that is, those who are filled with an unclean spirit.

1208
02:14:22,316 --> 02:14:24,634
” Therefore, you will be children of bloodshed.

1209
02:14:24,634 --> 02:14:27,544
For you do not desire the peace of the brothers, but blood.

1210
02:14:27,544 --> 02:14:29,813
Your faith is false, your belief is deceitful.

1211
02:14:29,813 --> 02:14:39,480
The heretical congregation is like an adulterous woman: for the Catholic Church has never left the bed and chamber of her husband from the beginning, nor has she desired other lovers or strangers.

1212
02:14:39,480 --> 02:14:50,873
You have painted an exiled form with a new color; you have separated your bed from the ancient marriage; you have departed from the body of the one true mother, adorned with a new kind of pleasing and new enticements of corruption.

1213
02:14:50,873 --> 02:15:08,973
You present the most blessed Cyprian to me as a witness against me because in the letter concerning the Lapsed, he says that Moses, Daniel, and Job prayed for sinners but did not succeed, as the Lord says: “Even if Noah, Job, and Daniel were in their midst, they would not save their sons or daughters, but they alone would be saved” (Ezekiel fourteen, verse twenty).

1214
02:15:08,973 --> 02:15:13,018
If only you would rely on Cyprian as a witness and agree with such sound opinions.

1215
02:15:13,018 --> 02:15:23,178
When urging the lapsed to repentance, who did not want to repent and claimed they had received peace from confessors or martyrs, he taught that even those patriarchs could not intercede for the unrepentant.

1216
02:15:23,178 --> 02:15:25,446
Indeed, who can free someone who is unwilling?

1217
02:15:25,446 --> 02:15:27,419
Who can humble themselves for the proud?

1218
02:15:27,419 --> 02:15:29,688
Who can intercede for those who do not repent?

1219
02:15:29,688 --> 02:15:33,288
When he said this, he was urging them towards the remedies of repentance.

1220
02:15:33,288 --> 02:15:40,489
A man of such seriousness and merit did not speak against himself but taught that sinners should offer prayers and practice confession diligently.

1221
02:15:41,327 --> 02:15:48,848
However, consider Cyprian's examples, where he notes that even Moses and other saints didn't always succeed in their petitions for sinners.

1222
02:15:48,848 --> 02:15:49,227
Really?

1223
02:15:49,227 --> 02:15:51,608
Don't you see for whom Moses didn't succeed?

1224
02:15:51,608 --> 02:15:54,908
When he returned to the people, what did he hear in the camp?

1225
02:15:54,908 --> 02:15:58,371
The voices of drunkards and the songs of idol worship resounded.

1226
02:15:58,371 --> 02:16:04,269
The people still persisted in wickedness, still remained in their very crimes, and didn't know how to repent.

1227
02:16:04,269 --> 02:16:07,136
Yet, who among us told you that Moses didn't succeed?

1228
02:16:07,136 --> 02:16:12,601
God had indeed said to him: "He has sinned before me, I will erase him from the book" (Exodus 32:33).

1229
02:16:12,601 --> 02:16:20,825
However, God spoke with the authority of a judge and the power of the Lord; but see how quickly he changed his sentence against the people's wickedness.

1230
02:16:20,825 --> 02:16:21,204
Listen.

1231
02:16:21,204 --> 02:16:29,266
